{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775884365683,"sessionID":"ses_2850b7bd3ffe3UepMOBdCsmkmc","part":{"id":"prt_d7af4e63f001E0vB3O5QhZCpSM","messageID":"msg_d7af4b4d6001VH7UDlXdHQs5mw","sessionID":"ses_2850b7bd3ffe3UepMOBdCsmkmc","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_functions.read:3","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/proposal.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/proposal.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # Proposal: CLI Binary Entry Points\n2: \n3: ## AR-019 вҖ” CLI дәҢиҝӣеҲ¶е…ҘеҸЈ (4 binaries)\n4: \n5: | Field | Value |\n6: |-------|-------|\n7: | **Module** | `cmd` |\n8: | **Language** | Go |\n9: | **Size** | M (Medium) |\n10: | **Status** | Proposed |\n11: \n12: ---\n13: \n14: ## Purpose\n15: \n16: Implement the CLI binary entry points for the 4 core AgentCube components. Each binary provides a standalone executable that initializes its respective service with proper configuration, dependency wiring, and graceful shutdown handling. This proposal delivers:\n17: \n18: 1. **agentd** вҖ” Idle cleanup controller binary that runs the Sandbox reconciler\n19: 2. **router** вҖ” HTTP session routing proxy with Gin framework\n20: 3. **workload-manager** вҖ” Sandbox orchestration controller with Kubernetes CRD management\n21: 4. **picod** вҖ” Sandbox daemon for code execution inside sandbox pods\n22: \n23: These binaries serve as the deployment targets for the AgentCube platform, enabling independent scaling, deployment, and lifecycle management of each component.\n24: \n25: ---\n26: \n27: ## Scope\n28: \n29: ### In Scope\n30: \n31: | Item | Detail |\n32: |------|--------|\n33: | **Binary Entry Points** | 4 `main.go` files under `cmd/`: `agentd`, `router`, `workload-manager`, `picod` |\n34: | **Flag Parsing** | Standard Go `flag` package with `--help` support |\n35: | **Configuration** | CLI flags for service-specific settings (ports, timeouts, Kubernetes config) |\n36: | **Graceful Shutdown** | SIGINT/SIGTERM handling with configurable timeout |\n37: | **Dependency Wiring** | Initialize clients (Redis, Kubernetes, HTTP) from configuration |\n38: | **Service Startup** | Start controllers, HTTP servers, and reconcilers |\n39: | **Health Checks** | Basic liveness/readiness endpoints where applicable |\n40: | **Logging** | Structured startup logging with version and configuration |\n41: \n42: ### Out of Scope\n43: \n44: - Configuration file support (YAML/JSON config files)\n45: - Hot configuration reloading\n46: - Service discovery integration (Consul, etcd)\n47: - Metrics and monitoring endpoints (Prometheus)\n48: - Distributed tracing (Jaeger, Zipkin)\n49: - Circuit breaker patterns\n50: - Multi-instance leader election\n51: - Automated TLS certificate management\n52: - Plugin system for extensibility\n53: \n54: ---\n55: \n56: ## Design\n57: \n58: ### File Structure\n59: \n60: | File | Role | Lines (est.) |\n61: |------|------|--------------|\n62: | `cmd/agentd/main.go` | Idle cleanup controller binary | ~80 |\n63: | `cmd/router/main.go` | Session routing proxy binary | ~100 |\n64: | `cmd/workload-manager/main.go` | Sandbox orchestration binary | ~120 |\n65: | `cmd/picod/main.go` | Sandbox daemon binary | ~90 |\n66: \n67: ### Architecture\n68: \n69: ```\n70: в”Ңв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”җ\n71: в”Ӯ                        AgentCube Platform                            в”Ӯ\n72: в”Ӯ                                                                      в”Ӯ\n73: в”Ӯ  в”Ңв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”җ  в”Ңв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”җ  в”Ңв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”җ  в”Ңв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”җ в”Ӯ\n74: в”Ӯ  в”Ӯ   agentd     в”Ӯ  в”Ӯ    router    в”Ӯ  в”Ӯworkload-mgr  в”Ӯ  в”Ӯ  picod   в”Ӯ в”Ӯ\n75: в”Ӯ  в”Ӯ  в”Ңв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”җ  в”Ӯ  в”Ӯ  в”Ңв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”җ  в”Ӯ  в”Ӯ  в”Ңв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”җ  в”Ӯ  в”Ӯ в”Ңв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”җ в”Ӯ в”Ӯ\n76: в”Ӯ  в”Ӯ  в”ӮReconcilerв”Ӯ  в”Ӯ  в”Ӯ  в”Ӯ  Gin   в”Ӯ  в”Ӯ  в”Ӯ  в”ӮControllerв”Ӯ  в”Ӯ  в”Ӯ в”Ӯ HTTP в”Ӯ в”Ӯ в”Ӯ\n77: в”Ӯ  в”Ӯ  в”Ӯ(controllerв”Ӯ  в”Ӯ  в”Ӯ  в”ӮServer  в”Ӯ  в”Ӯ  в”Ӯ  в”Ӯ + API    в”Ӯ  в”Ӯ  в”Ӯ в”ӮServerв”Ӯ в”Ӯ в”Ӯ\n78: в”Ӯ  в”Ӯ  в”Ӯ-runtime) в”Ӯ  в”Ӯ  в”Ӯ  в”Ӯ        в”Ӯ  в”Ӯ  в”Ӯ  в”Ӯ Server   в”Ӯ  в”Ӯ  в”Ӯ в”Ӯ      в”Ӯ в”Ӯ в”Ӯ\n79: в”Ӯ  в”Ӯ  в””в”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”¬в”Җв”Җв”Җв”ҳ  в”Ӯ  в”Ӯ  в””в”Җв”Җв”Җв”¬в”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”ҳ  в”Ӯ  в”Ӯ  в””в”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”¬в”Җв”Җв”Җв”ҳ  в”Ӯ  в”Ӯ в””в”Җв”Җв”¬в”Җв”Җв”Җв”ҳ в”Ӯ в”Ӯ\n80: в”Ӯ  в”Ӯ       в”Ӯ      в”Ӯ  в”Ӯ      в”Ӯ       в”Ӯ  в”Ӯ       в”Ӯ      в”Ӯ  в”Ӯ    в”Ӯ     в”Ӯ в”Ӯ\n81: в”Ӯ  в”Ӯ  K8s API    в”Ӯ  в”Ӯ  Redis/Store в”Ӯ  в”Ӯ  K8s API      в”Ӯ  в”Ӯ Workspace в”Ӯ в”Ӯ\n82: в”Ӯ  в”Ӯ       в”Ӯ      в”Ӯ  в”Ӯ      в”Ӯ       в”Ӯ  в”Ӯ       в”Ӯ      в”Ӯ  в”Ӯ    в”Ӯ     в”Ӯ в”Ӯ\n83: в”Ӯ  в””в”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”јв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”ҳ  в””в”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”јв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”ҳ  в””в”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”јв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”ҳ  в””в”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”јв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”ҳ в”Ӯ\n84: в”Ӯ          в”Ӯ                в”Ӯ                  в”Ӯ              в”Ӯ       в”Ӯ\n85: в”Ӯ          в””в”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”ҙв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”ҙв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”ҳ       в”Ӯ\n86: в”Ӯ                              в”Ӯ                                       в”Ӯ\n87: в”Ӯ                    Kubernetes Cluster                               в”Ӯ\n88: в”Ӯ                         + Redis/Valkey                              в”Ӯ\n89: в””в”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”ҳ\n90: ```\n91: \n92: ### Binary Responsibilities\n93: \n94: #### agentd\n95: - Parse Kubernetes configuration flags\n96: - Initialize controller-runtime Manager with Sandbox scheme\n97: - Start idle cleanup reconciler\n98: - Handle graceful shutdown on signals\n99: \n100: #### router\n101: - Parse HTTP port and Redis connection flags\n102: - Initialize Gin HTTP server\n103: - Wire session routing middleware\n104: - Connect to workload manager backend\n105: - Handle graceful HTTP server shutdown\n106: \n107: #### workload-manager\n108: - Parse Kubernetes and Redis configuration\n109: - Initialize Sandbox controller (reconciler)\n110: - Start HTTP API server for sandbox management\n111: - Handle CRD lifecycle operations\n112: - Coordinate with optional Volcano scheduler\n113: \n114: #### picod\n115: - Parse HTTP port and workspace root flags\n116: - Initialize workspace directory\n117: - Start code execution HTTP handlers\n118: - Provide file upload/download endpoints\n119: - Support exec streaming for interactive sessions\n120: \n121: ---\n122: \n123: ## Execution Flows\n124: \n125: ### Common Binary Startup Flow\n126: \n127: ```\n128: main()\n129:     в”Ӯ\n130:     в–ј\n131: в”Ңв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”җ\n132: в”Ӯ Parse Flags   в”Ӯ\n133: в””в”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”¬в”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”ҳ\n134:         в”Ӯ\n135:         в–ј\n136: в”Ңв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”җ\n137: в”Ӯ Validate      в”Ӯ\n138: в”Ӯ Required Flagsв”Ӯ\n139: в””в”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”¬в”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”ҳ\n140:         в”Ӯ\n141:         в”ңв”Җ Missing в”Җв”Җв–ә Print Error + Exit(1)\n142:         в”Ӯ\n143:         в–ј\n144: в”Ңв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”җ\n145: в”Ӯ Log Startup   в”Ӯ\n146: в”Ӯ (version, cfg)в”Ӯ\n147: в””в”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”¬в”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”ҳ\n148:         в”Ӯ\n149:         в–ј\n150: в”Ңв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”җ\n151: в”Ӯ Initialize    в”Ӯ\n152: в”Ӯ Dependencies  в”Ӯ\n153: в””в”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”¬в”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”ҳ\n154:         в”Ӯ\n155:         в–ј\n156: в”Ңв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”җ\n157: в”Ӯ Start Service в”Ӯ\n158: в”Ӯ (blocking)    в”Ӯ\n159: в””в”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”¬в”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”ҳ\n160:         в”Ӯ\n161:         в–ј\n162: в”Ңв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”җ\n163: в”Ӯ Wait for      в”Ӯ\n164: в”Ӯ SIGINT/SIGTERMв”Ӯ\n165: в””в”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”¬в”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”ҳ\n166:         в”Ӯ\n167:         в–ј\n168: в”Ңв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”җ\n169: в”Ӯ Graceful      в”Ӯ\n170: в”Ӯ Shutdown      в”Ӯ\n171: в””в”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”¬в”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”ҳ\n172:         в”Ӯ\n173:         в–ј\n174:     Exit(0)\n175: ```\n176: \n177: ### agentd Startup Flow\n178: \n179: ```\n180: main()\n181:     в”Ӯ\n182:     в–ј\n183: Parse flags: --kubeconfig, --sync-period\n184:     в”Ӯ\n185:     в–ј\n186: ctrl.GetConfigOrDie() // K8s config\n187:     в”Ӯ\n188:     в–ј\n189: scheme := runtime.NewScheme()\n190:     в”Ӯ\n191:     в–ј\n192: Add Sandbox v1alpha1 to scheme\n193:     в”Ӯ\n194:     в–ј\n195: ctrl.NewManager(ctrl.Options{\n196:     Scheme: scheme,\n197:     SyncPeriod: syncPeriod,\n198: })\n199:     в”Ӯ\n200:     в–ј\n201: agentd.NewReconciler(mgr.GetClient())\n202:     в”Ӯ\n203:     в–ј\n204: SetupWithManager(mgr)\n205:     в”Ӯ\n206:     в–ј\n207: mgr.Start(ctrl.SetupSignalHandler())\n208: ```\n209: \n210: ### router Startup Flow\n211: \n212: ```\n213: main()\n214:     в”Ӯ\n215:     в–ј\n216: Parse flags: --port, --redis-addr, --workload-manager\n217:     в”Ӯ\n218:     в–ј\n219: Validate required flags\n220:     в”Ӯ\n221:     в–ј\n222: redis.NewClient(redisAddr)\n223:     в”Ӯ\n224:     в–ј\n225: store := router.NewSessionStore(redis)\n226:     в”Ӯ\n227:     в–ј\n228: gin.New()\n229:     в”Ӯ\n230:     в–ј\n231: router.SetupRoutes(engine, store, workloadMgrURL)\n232:     в”Ӯ\n233:     в–ј\n234: http.ListenAndServe()\n235:     в”Ӯ\n236:     в–ј\n237: Signal handling for graceful shutdown\n238: ```\n239: \n240: ### workload-manager Startup Flow\n241: \n242: ```\n243: main()\n244:     в”Ӯ\n245:     в–ј\n246: Parse flags: --port, --kubeconfig, --redis-addr, --default-image\n247:     в”Ӯ\n248:     в–ј\n249: ctrl.GetConfigOrDie()\n250:     в”Ӯ\n251:     в–ј\n252: scheme := runtime.NewScheme()\n253: Add AgentRuntime/CodeInterpreter to scheme\n254:     в”Ӯ\n255:     в–ј\n256: ctrl.NewManager(...)\n257:     в”Ӯ\n258:     в–ј\n259: workloadmanager.NewController(mgr, redis, config)\n260:     в”Ӯ\n261:     в–ј\n262: Setup HTTP API server on --port\n263:     в”Ӯ\n264:     в–ј\n265: Start both controller and HTTP server\n266: ```\n267: \n268: ### picod Startup Flow\n269: \n270: ```\n271: main()\n272:     в”Ӯ\n273:     в–ј\n274: Parse flags: --port, --workspace\n275:     в”Ӯ\n276:     в–ј\n277: Resolve workspace to absolute path\n278: Create if not exists\n279:     в”Ӯ\n280:     в–ј\n281: Validate workspace is writable\n282:     в”Ӯ\n283:     в–ј\n284: http.NewServeMux()\n285:     в”Ӯ\n286:     в–ј\n287: Register handlers:\n288:   - /execute (code execution)\n289:   - /upload (file upload)\n290:   - /download (file download)\n291:   - /exec (interactive exec)\n292:     в”Ӯ\n293:     в–ј\n294: http.ListenAndServe()\n295: ```\n296: \n297: ---\n298: \n299: ## Interface\n300: \n301: ### agentd Flags\n302: \n303: | Flag | Type | Default | Description |\n304: |------|------|---------|-------------|\n305: | `--kubeconfig` | string | \"\" | Path to kubeconfig (empty = in-cluster) |\n306: | `--sync-period` | duration | 5m | Full sync period for all sandboxes |\n307: | `--graceful-timeout` | duration | 30s | Graceful shutdown timeout |\n308: | `--help` | bool | false | Print usage and exit |\n309: \n310: ### router Flags\n311: \n312: | Flag | Type | Default | Description |\n313: |------|------|---------|-------------|\n314: | `--port` | int | 8080 | HTTP server port |\n315: | `--debug` | bool | false | Enable debug logging |\n316: | `--redis-addr` | string | (required) | Redis/Valkey server address |\n317: | `--workload-manager` | string | (required) | Workload manager URL |\n318: | `--graceful-timeout` | duration | 30s | Graceful shutdown timeout |\n319: | `--help` | bool | false | Print usage and exit |\n320: \n321: ### workload-manager Flags\n322: \n323: | Flag | Type | Default | Description |\n324: |------|------|---------|-------------|\n325: | `--port` | int | 8080 | HTTP API server port |\n326: | `--kubeconfig` | string | \"\" | Path to kubeconfig (empty = in-cluster) |\n327: | `--redis-addr` | string | (required) | Redis/Valkey server address |\n328: | `--default-image` | string | \"ubuntu:22.04\" | Default sandbox image |\n329: | `--namespace` | string | \"default\" | Default namespace |\n330: | `--graceful-timeout` | duration | 30s | Graceful shutdown timeout |\n331: | `--help` | bool | false | Print usage and exit |\n332: \n333: ### picod Flags\n334: \n335: | Flag | Type | Default | Description |\n336: |------|------|---------|-------------|\n337: | `--port` | int | 8080 | HTTP server port |\n338: | `--workspace` | string | \".\" | Workspace root directory |\n339: | `--read-header-timeout` | duration | 10s | HTTP read header timeout |\n340: | `--help` | bool | false | Print usage and exit |\n341: \n342: ---\n343: \n344: ## Error Handling\n345: \n346: ### Error Types\n347: \n348: | Error | Description | Binary |\n349: |-------|-------------|--------|\n350: | `FlagError` | Missing or invalid CLI flags | All |\n351: | `ConfigError` | Kubernetes config loading failure | agentd, workload-manager |\n352: | `ConnectionError` | Redis/Valkey connection failure | router, workload-manager |\n353: | `SchemeError` | CRD scheme registration failure | agentd, workload-manager |\n354: | `ServerError` | HTTP server startup failure | router, workload-manager, picod |\n355: | `WorkspaceError` | Workspace initialization failure | picod |\n356: \n357: ### Exit Codes\n358: \n359: | Exit Code | Meaning |\n360: |-----------|---------|\n361: | 0 | Clean shutdown |\n362: | 1 | Configuration error |\n363: | 2 | Dependency initialization error |\n364: | 3 | Server startup error |\n365: | 130 | Interrupted (SIGINT) |\n366: | 143 | Terminated (SIGTERM) |\n367: \n368: ---\n369: \n370: ## Security Considerations\n371: \n372: ### RBAC Requirements\n373: \n374: #### agentd\n375: | Resource | Verbs |\n376: |----------|-------|\n377: | `sandboxes` | `get`, `list`, `watch`, `delete` |\n378: \n379: #### router\n380: | Resource | Verbs |\n381: |----------|-------|\n382: | `secrets` | `get`, `list`, `watch`, `create`, `update`, `patch`, `delete` |\n383: \n384: #### workload-manager\n385: | Resource | Verbs |\n386: |----------|-------|\n387: | `agentruntimes` | `get`, `list`, `watch` |\n388: | `codeinterpreters` | `get`, `list`, `watch`, `create`, `update`, `patch`, `delete` |\n389: | `pods` | `get`, `list`, `watch` |\n390: | `secrets` | `get`, `list`, `watch`, `create`, `update`, `patch`, `delete` |\n391: \n392: #### picod\n393: - Runs inside sandbox pod with container-local permissions\n394: - Workspace directory isolation\n395: - No Kubernetes API access required\n396: \n397: ### Sensitive Data\n398: - Redis passwords via environment variables (not flags)\n399: - Kubernetes service account tokens (in-cluster) or kubeconfig files\n400: - No secrets logged at startup\n401: \n402: ---\n403: \n404: ## Impact Analysis\n405: \n406: ### Files Created\n407: \n408: | File | Lines (est.) | Description |\n409: |------|--------------|-------------|\n410: | `cmd/agentd/main.go` | ~80 | Idle cleanup controller entry point |\n411: | `cmd/router/main.go` | ~100 | Session routing proxy entry point |\n412: | `cmd/workload-manager/main.go` | ~120 | Sandbox orchestration entry point |\n413: | `cmd/picod/main.go` | ~90 | Sandbox daemon entry point |\n414: \n415: ### Dependencies\n416: \n417: ```go\n418: import (\n419:     \"flag\"\n420:     \"os\"\n421:     \"os/signal\"\n422:     \"syscall\"\n423:     \"time\"\n424:     \"context\"\n425:     \n426:     // Kubernetes\n427:     \"k8s.io/client-go/tools/clientcmd\"\n428:     \"sigs.k8s.io/controller-runtime\"\n429:     \n430:     // HTTP\n431:     \"github.com/gin-gonic/gin\"\n432:     \n433:     // Storage\n434:     \"github.com/redis/go-redis/v9\"\n435:     \"github.com/valkey-io/valkey-go\"\n436:     \n437:     // AgentCube internal\n438:     \"github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/agentd\"\n439:     \"github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/router\"\n440:     \"github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/workloadmanager\"\n441:     \"github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/picod\"\n442:     \"github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1\"\n443: )\n444: ```\n445: \n446: | Package | Purpose |\n447: |---------|---------|\n448: | `sigs.k8s.io/controller-runtime` | Kubernetes controller framework |\n449: | `k8s.io/client-go/tools/clientcmd` | K8s config loading |\n450: | `github.com/gin-gonic/gin` | HTTP framework for router |\n451: | `github.com/redis/go-redis/v9` | Redis client |\n452: | `github.com/valkey-io/valkey-go` | Valkey client |\n453: \n454: ### Downstream Consumers\n455: \n456: | Consumer | Usage |\n457: |----------|-------|\n458: | Helm Charts | Deploy binaries as container images |\n459: | Dockerfiles | Build container images for each binary |\n460: | CI/CD | Build and test binaries |\n461: | Local Development | Run services locally with `go run` |\n462: \n463: ### Performance Characteristics\n464: \n465: | Binary | Memory (est.) | Startup Time | Notes |\n466: |--------|---------------|--------------|-------|\n467: | agentd | ~50MB | <5s | Reconciler only, no HTTP server |\n468: | router | ~30MB | <3s | Depends on Redis connection |\n469: | workload-manager | ~60MB | <5s | Controller + HTTP server |\n470: | picod | ~20MB | <2s | Lightweight daemon |\n471: \n472: ---\n473: \n474: ## Alternatives Considered\n475: \n476: ### Alternative 1: Single Binary with Subcommands\n477: \n478: | Aspect | Evaluation |\n479: |--------|------------|\n480: | **Pros** | Simpler deployment; single artifact; shared code |\n481: | **Cons** | Larger binary size; violates microservices pattern; harder to scale independently; all components must be updated together |\n482: | **Decision** | **Rejected** вҖ” AgentCube follows microservices architecture; independent scaling and deployment are requirements |\n483: \n484: ### Alternative 2: Configuration Files Instead of Flags\n485: \n486: | Aspect | Evaluation |\n487: |--------|------------|\n488: | **Pros** | More configuration options; easier to manage complex configs; version controlled |\n489: | **Cons** | Additional file management; less explicit; harder to debug; requires config reloading logic |\n490: | **Decision** | **Rejected** вҖ” Flags are simpler for containerized environments (12-factor app); config files can be added later if needed |\n491: \n492: ### Alternative 3: Environment Variables Only\n493: \n494: | Aspect | Evaluation |\n495: |--------|------------|\n496: | **Pros** | Cloud-native; works well with Kubernetes secrets; no command-line exposure |\n497: | **Cons** | Less discoverable; no built-in help; harder to validate at startup |\n498: | **Decision** | **Rejected** вҖ” Flags provide better UX and discoverability; env vars can supplement flags for secrets |\n499: \n500: ### Alternative 4: Sidecar Pattern for picod\n501: \n502: | Aspect | Evaluation |\n503: |--------|------------|\n504: | **Pros** | Separation of concerns; independent updates |\n505: | **Cons** | More complex deployment; networking overhead; requires shared filesystem |\n506: | **Decision** | **Rejected** вҖ” picod is designed to run inside sandbox pods as the main process; sidecar adds unnecessary complexity |\n507: \n508: ---\n509: \n510: ## Risks and Mitigations\n511: \n512: | Risk | Likelihood | Impact | Mitigation |\n513: |------|------------|--------|------------|\n514: | Flag parsing inconsistencies across binaries | Medium | Low | Use shared flag helper functions; consistent naming conventions |\n515: | Missing required flags in production | Medium | High | Fail fast with clear error messages; validate all required flags before startup |\n516: | Graceful shutdown timeout too short | Low | Medium | Configurable timeout with sensible default (30s); log warnings on timeout |\n517: | Kubernetes config loading failures | Medium | High | Support both in-cluster and external configs; clear error messages |\n518: | Redis connection failures at startup | Medium | High | Retry with exponential backoff; fail fast after retries |\n519: | Binary size bloat from dependencies | Low | Medium | Use build flags `-ldflags=\"-s -w\"`; multi-stage Docker builds |\n520: | Signal handling race conditions | Low | Medium | Use context-based shutdown; proper goroutine synchronization |\n521: | Port conflicts | Low | Medium | Configurable ports; check port availability; clear error messages |\n522: \n523: ---\n524: \n525: ## Verification\n526: \n527: ### Build Verification\n528: \n529: ```bash\n530: # Build all binaries\n531: go build -o bin/agentd ./cmd/agentd\n532: go build -o bin/router ./cmd/router\n533: go build -o bin/workload-manager ./cmd/workload-manager\n534: go build -o bin/picod ./cmd/picod\n535: \n536: # Verify binaries exist\n537: ls -la bin/\n538: ```\n539: \n540: ### Help Verification\n541: \n542: ```bash\n543: # Each binary should print help\n544: ./bin/agentd --help\n545: ./bin/router --help\n546: ./bin/workload-manager --help\n547: ./bin/picod --help\n548: ```\n549: \n550: ### Startup Verification (Local)\n551: \n552: ```bash\n553: # Test picod (no external deps)\n554: ./bin/picod --port=18080 &\n555: sleep 1\n556: curl http://localhost:18080/health || echo \"Health check not implemented yet\"\n557: kill %1\n558: \n559: # Test agentd (requires K8s config, will fail gracefully)\n560: ./bin/agentd --kubeconfig=/dev/null 2>&1 | head -5\n561: \n562: # Test with missing required flags\n563: ./bin/router 2>&1 | grep -q \"required\" && echo \"Flag validation works\"\n564: ```\n565: \n566: ### Graceful Shutdown Test\n567: \n568: ```bash\n569: # Test graceful shutdown\n570: timeout 2 ./bin/picod --port=18081 &\n571: sleep 0.5\n572: kill -TERM %1\n573: wait %1\n574: echo \"Exit code: $?\"  # Should be 0\n575: ```\n576: \n577: ### Docker Build Verification\n578: \n579: ```bash\n580: # Build container images\n581: make docker-build\n582: \n583: # Verify images\n584: docker images | grep agentcube\n585: ```\n586: \n587: ---\n588: \n589: ## References\n590: \n591: - [AR-019 Delta Spec](changes/AR-019/delta-spec.md) вҖ” Detailed requirements\n592: - [client-go Library](deployment/client-go.md) вҖ” Kubernetes client patterns\n593: - [Deployment Design](deployment/design.md) вҖ” Helm charts and Dockerfiles\n594: - [CLI Toolkit Design](cli-toolkit/design.md) вҖ” Python CLI design\n595: - [project.md](project.md) вҖ” Project context and architecture\n596: \n597: ---\n598: \n599: ## Success Criteria\n600: \n601: 1. вң… All 4 binaries compile without errors\n602: 2. вң… Each binary prints help with `--help` flag\n603: 3. вң… Each binary validates required flags and exits with error if missing\n604: 4. вң… agentd starts controller-runtime manager with Sandbox reconciler\n605: 5. вң… router starts Gin HTTP server and connects to Redis\n606: 6. вң… workload-manager starts controller and HTTP API server\n607: 7. вң… picod starts HTTP server and initializes workspace\n608: 8. вң… All binaries handle SIGINT/SIGTERM for graceful shutdown\n609: 9. вң… Exit codes are correct (0 for success, non-zero for errors)\n610: 10. вң… Docker builds succeed for all binaries\n611: 11. вң… Binaries log startup messages with version and configuration\n612: \n613: ---\n614: \n615: *AR-019 вҖ” Module: cmd вҖ” Language: Go вҖ” Size: M*\n\n(End of file - total 615 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# Proposal: CLI Binary Entry Points\n\n## AR-019 вҖ” CLI дәҢиҝӣеҲ¶е…ҘеҸЈ (4 binaries)\n\n| Field | Value |\n|-------|-------|\n| **Module** | `cmd` |\n| **Language** | Go |\n| **Size** | M (Medium) |\n| **Status** | Proposed |\n\n---\n\n## Purpose\n\nImplement the CLI binary entry points for the 4 core AgentCube components. Each binary provides a standalone executable that initializes its respective service with proper configuration, dependency wiring, and graceful shutdown handling. This proposal delivers:\n\n1. **agentd** вҖ” Idle cleanup controller binary that runs the Sandbox reconciler\n2. **router** вҖ” HTTP session routing proxy with Gin framework\n3. **workload-manager** вҖ” Sandbox orchestration controller with Kubernetes CRD management","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/proposal.md","time":{"start":1775884365647,"end":1775884365681}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775884365698,"sessionID":"ses_2850b7bd3ffe3UepMOBdCsmkmc","part":{"id":"prt_d7af4ea97001XWr7mfWNRbWv7J","messageID":"msg_d7af4b4d6001VH7UDlXdHQs5mw","sessionID":"ses_2850b7bd3ffe3UepMOBdCsmkmc","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_functions.read:4","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-019/tasks.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-019/tasks.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-019 вҖ” CLI дәҢиҝӣеҲ¶е…ҘеҸЈ (4 binaries)\n2: \n3: > **Module:** `cmd`  \n4: > **Language:** Go  \n5: > **Size:** M  \n6: > **Stage:** ST-3 (Design) Completed вҶ’ ST-4 (Implementation)  \n7: > **Base Spec:** project.md, deployment/design.md\n8: \n9: ---\n10: \n11: ## Overview\n12: \n13: AR-019 implements the CLI binary entry points for the 4 core AgentCube components:\n14: 1. **agentd** - Idle cleanup controller binary\n15: 2. **router** - Session routing proxy binary  \n16: 3. **workload-manager** - Sandbox orchestration binary\n17: 4. **picod** - Sandbox daemon binary\n18: \n19: Each binary SHALL parse CLI flags, initialize configuration, wire dependencies, start the respective service, and handle graceful shutdown via OS signals.\n20: \n21: ---\n22: \n23: ## ST-4.1 вҖ” Common Infrastructure\n24: \n25: ### 4.1.1 Signal Handling Package\n26: \n27: | # | Task | Verification | Est. |\n28: |---|------|--------------|------|\n29: | 4.1.1.1 | Create `pkg/common/signal` package | Directory exists | 0.25h |\n30: | 4.1.1.2 | Implement `SetupSignalHandler()` returning `<-chan struct{}` | Function exists and compiles | 0.5h |\n31: | 4.1.1.3 | Handle SIGINT and SIGTERM | Test with `kill -INT` and `kill -TERM` | 0.25h |\n32: | 4.1.1.4 | Implement graceful timeout handling | Channel closes after signal received | 0.25h |\n33: \n34: **Deliverable:** `pkg/common/signal` package with signal handling utilities.\n35: \n36: ### 4.1.2 Version Package\n37: \n38: | # | Task | Verification | Est. |\n39: |---|------|--------------|------|\n40: | 4.1.2.1 | Create `pkg/common/version` package | Directory exists | 0.25h |\n41: | 4.1.2.2 | Define `var Version = \"dev\"` for ldflags injection | Variable exists and exported | 0.25h |\n42: | 4.1.2.3 | Add `PrintVersion(binaryName string)` function | Prints \"binaryName version: {Version}\" | 0.25h |\n43: | 4.1.2.4 | Add `--version` flag support pattern | Document in spec | 0.25h |\n44: \n45: **Deliverable:** Version package for consistent version reporting across binaries.\n46: \n47: ---\n48: \n49: ## ST-4.2 вҖ” Agentd Binary Entry Point\n50: \n51: ### 4.2.1 Directory and File Structure\n52: \n53: | # | Task | Verification | Est. |\n54: |---|------|--------------|------|\n55: | 4.2.1.1 | Ensure `cmd/agentd/` directory exists | `ls cmd/agentd/` succeeds | 0.25h |\n56: | 4.2.1.2 | Create `cmd/agentd/main.go` | File compiles | 0.25h |\n57: \n58: ### 4.2.2 Flag Parsing\n59: \n60: | # | Task | Verification | Est. |\n61: |---|------|--------------|------|\n62: | 4.2.2.1 | Define `--kubeconfig` flag (string, default: \"\") | `flag.String(\"kubeconfig\", \"\", \"...\")` | 0.25h |\n63: | 4.2.2.2 | Define `--sync-period` flag (duration, default: 5m) | `flag.Duration(\"sync-period\", 5*time.Minute, \"...\")` | 0.25h |\n64: | 4.2.2.3 | Define `--graceful-timeout` flag (duration, default: 30s) | `flag.Duration(\"graceful-timeout\", 30*time.Second, \"...\")` | 0.25h |\n65: | 4.2.2.4 | Call `flag.Parse()` in main | Flags parse correctly | 0.25h |\n66: \n67: ### 4.2.3 Manager Construction\n68: \n69: | # | Task | Verification | Est. |\n70: |---|------|--------------|------|\n71: | 4.2.3.1 | Import `sigs.k8s.io/controller-runtime/pkg/manager` | Import resolves | 0.25h |\n72: | 4.2.3.2 | Import `k8s.io/client-go/tools/clientcmd` | Import resolves | 0.25h |\n73: | 4.2.3.3 | Build Kubernetes config (in-cluster or from kubeconfig) | Config builds without error | 0.5h |\n74: | 4.2.3.4 | Create manager with Scheme containing sandboxv1alpha1 | Manager creates successfully | 0.5h |\n75: | 4.2.3.5 | Disable metrics server (`BindAddress: \"0\"`) | Manager starts without metrics | 0.25h |\n76: | 4.2.3.6 | Disable health probe server (`HealthProbeBindAddress: \"0\"`) | Manager starts without probes | 0.25h |\n77: \n78: ### 4.2.4 Reconciler Setup\n79: \n80: | # | Task | Verification | Est. |\n81: |---|------|--------------|------|\n82: | 4.2.4.1 | Import `pkg/agentd` reconciler package | Import resolves | 0.25h |\n83: | 4.2.4.2 | Create reconciler instance with manager client | Reconciler creates | 0.25h |\n84: | 4.2.4.3 | Setup reconciler with manager using `ctrl.NewControllerManagedBy` | Controller registered | 0.5h |\n85: \n86: ### 4.2.5 Graceful Shutdown\n87: \n88: | # | Task | Verification | Est. |\n89: |---|------|--------------|------|\n90: | 4.2.5.1 | Set up signal handler for SIGINT/SIGTERM | `signal.SetupSignalHandler()` | 0.25h |\n91: | 4.2.5.2 | Start manager in goroutine | `go mgr.Start(ctx)` | 0.25h |\n92: | 4.2.5.3 | Wait for signal then gracefully stop | `<-signalChan` triggers shutdown | 0.25h |\n93: | 4.2.5.4 | Implement graceful timeout handling | Shutdown completes within timeout | 0.25h |\n94: \n95: **Deliverable:** `cmd/agentd/main.go` compiles and runs with flag parsing.\n96: \n97: ---\n98: \n99: ## ST-4.3 вҖ” Router Binary Entry Point\n100: \n101: ### 4.3.1 Directory and File Structure\n102: \n103: | # | Task | Verification | Est. |\n104: |---|------|--------------|------|\n105: | 4.3.1.1 | Ensure `cmd/router/` directory exists | `ls cmd/router/` succeeds | 0.25h |\n106: | 4.3.1.2 | Create `cmd/router/main.go` | File compiles | 0.25h |\n107: \n108: ### 4.3.2 Flag Parsing\n109: \n110: | # | Task | Verification | Est. |\n111: |---|------|--------------|------|\n112: | 4.3.2.1 | Define `--port` flag (int, default: 8080) | `flag.Int(\"port\", 8080, \"...\")` | 0.25h |\n113: | 4.3.2.2 | Define `--debug` flag (bool, default: false) | `flag.Bool(\"debug\", false, \"...\")` | 0.25h |\n114: | 4.3.2.3 | Define `--redis-addr` flag (string, required) | Flag defined, validation in code | 0.25h |\n115: | 4.3.2.4 | Define `--workload-manager` flag (string, required) | Flag defined, validation in code | 0.25h |\n116: | 4.3.2.5 | Define `--graceful-timeout` flag (duration, default: 30s) | `flag.Duration(\"graceful-timeout\", 30*time.Second, \"...\")` | 0.25h |\n117: | 4.3.2.6 | Validate required flags after `flag.Parse()` | Exits with error if missing | 0.5h |\n118: \n119: ### 4.3.3 Server Construction\n120: \n121: | # | Task | Verification | Est. |\n122: |---|------|--------------|------|\n123: | 4.3.3.1 | Import `github.com/gin-gonic/gin` | Import resolves | 0.25h |\n124: | 4.3.3.2 | Create Gin router instance | `gin.New()` or `gin.Default()` | 0.25h |\n125: | 4.3.3.3 | Set Gin mode based on `--debug` flag | `gin.SetMode(gin.DebugMode/ReleaseMode)` | 0.25h |\n126: | 4.3.3.4 | Import `pkg/router` package | Import resolves | 0.25h |\n127: | 4.3.3.5 | Wire router handlers and middleware | Routes registered | 0.5h |\n128: | 4.3.3.6 | Create HTTP server with configured port | `&http.Server{Addr: fmt.Sprintf(\":%d\", *port)}` | 0.25h |\n129: \n130: ### 4.3.4 Graceful Shutdown\n131: \n132: | # | Task | Verification | Est. |\n133: |---|------|--------------|------|\n134: | 4.3.4.1 | Start HTTP server in goroutine | `go server.ListenAndServe()` | 0.25h |\n135: | 4.3.4.2 | Set up signal handler | `signal.SetupSignalHandler()` | 0.25h |\n136: | 4.3.4.3 | Implement graceful shutdown with timeout | `server.Shutdown(ctx)` with timeout | 0.5h |\n137: \n138: **Deliverable:** `cmd/router/main.go` compiles and runs with flag parsing.\n139: \n140: ---\n141: \n142: ## ST-4.4 вҖ” Workload Manager Binary Entry Point\n143: \n144: ### 4.4.1 Directory and File Structure\n145: \n146: | # | Task | Verification | Est. |\n147: |---|------|---------