: | 4.4.4.2 | Start HTTP server in goroutine | Server starts | 0.25h |\n179: | 4.4.4.3 | Set up signal handler | `signal.SetupSignalHandler()` | 0.25h |\n180: | 4.4.4.4 | Implement graceful shutdown for both components | Both shutdown cleanly | 0.5h |\n181: \n182: **Deliverable:** `cmd/workload-manager/main.go` compiles and runs with flag parsing.\n183: \n184: ---\n185: \n186: ## ST-4.5 вҖ” Picod Binary Entry Point\n187: \n188: ### 4.5.1 Directory and File Structure\n189: \n190: | # | Task | Verification | Est. |\n191: |---|------|--------------|------|\n192: | 4.5.1.1 | Ensure `cmd/picod/` directory exists | `ls cmd/picod/` succeeds | 0.25h |\n193: | 4.5.1.2 | Create `cmd/picod/main.go` | File compiles | 0.25h |\n194: \n195: ### 4.5.2 Flag Parsing\n196: \n197: | # | Task | Verification | Est. |\n198: |---|------|--------------|------|\n199: | 4.5.2.1 | Define `--port` flag (int, default: 8080) | `flag.Int(\"port\", 8080, \"...\")` | 0.25h |\n200: | 4.5.2.2 | Define `--workspace` flag (string, default: \".\") | `flag.String(\"workspace\", \".\", \"...\")` | 0.25h |\n201: | 4.5.2.3 | Define `--read-header-timeout` flag (duration, default: 10s) | `flag.Duration(\"read-header-timeout\", 10*time.Second, \"...\")` | 0.25h |\n202: \n203: ### 4.5.3 Workspace Resolution\n204: \n205: | # | Task | Verification | Est. |\n206: |---|------|--------------|------|\n207: | 4.5.3.1 | Resolve workspace to absolute path | `filepath.Abs(*workspace)` | 0.25h |\n208: | 4.5.3.2 | Create workspace directory if not exists | `os.MkdirAll(workspace, 0755)` | 0.25h |\n209: | 4.5.3.3 | Handle directory creation errors | Logs fatal error on failure | 0.25h |\n210: \n211: ### 4.5.4 Server Construction\n212: \n213: | # | Task | Verification | Est. |\n214: |---|------|--------------|------|\n215: | 4.5.4.1 | Import `pkg/picod` package | Import resolves | 0.25h |\n216: | 4.5.4.2 | Create picod Config struct from flags | Config populated | 0.25h |\n217: | 4.5.4.3 | Construct picod server | `picod.NewServer(config)` | 0.5h |\n218: | 4.5.4.4 | Create HTTP server with ReadHeaderTimeout | `&http.Server{ReadHeaderTimeout: *readHeaderTimeout}` | 0.25h |\n219: \n220: ### 4.5.5 Graceful Shutdown\n221: \n222: | # | Task | Verification | Est. |\n223: |---|------|--------------|------|\n224: | 4.5.5.1 | Start server in goroutine | `go server.ListenAndServe()` | 0.25h |\n225: | 4.5.5.2 | Set up signal handler | `signal.SetupSignalHandler()` | 0.25h |\n226: | 4.5.5.3 | Implement graceful shutdown | `server.Shutdown(ctx)` with timeout | 0.25h |\n227: \n228: **Deliverable:** `cmd/picod/main.go` compiles and runs with flag parsing.\n229: \n230: ---\n231: \n232: ## ST-4.6 вҖ” Build Verification\n233: \n234: | # | Task | Verification | Est. |\n235: |---|------|--------------|------|\n236: | 4.6.1 | Verify `go build ./cmd/agentd/...` succeeds | Binary builds | 0.25h |\n237: | 4.6.2 | Verify `go build ./cmd/router/...` succeeds | Binary builds | 0.25h |\n238: | 4.6.3 | Verify `go build ./cmd/workload-manager/...` succeeds | Binary builds | 0.25h |\n239: | 4.6.4 | Verify `go build ./cmd/picod/...` succeeds | Binary builds | 0.25h |\n240: | 4.6.5 | Test `--help` on all binaries | Each prints usage | 0.25h |\n241: \n242: ---\n243: \n244: ## Verification Commands\n245: \n246: ```bash\n247: # Build all binaries\n248: go build -o bin/agentd ./cmd/agentd\n249: go build -o bin/router ./cmd/router\n250: go build -o bin/workload-manager ./cmd/workload-manager\n251: go build -o bin/picod ./cmd/picod\n252: \n253: # Verify help output\n254: ./bin/agentd --help\n255: ./bin/router --help\n256: ./bin/workload-manager --help\n257: ./bin/picod --help\n258: \n259: # Quick smoke test (will fail without deps, but verifies startup)\n260: timeout 2 ./bin/picod --port=18080 2>&1 || true\n261: timeout 2 ./bin/agentd --sync-period=1s 2>&1 || true\n262: ```\n263: \n264: ---\n265: \n266: ## Acceptance Criteria\n267: \n268: - [ ] `cmd/agentd/main.go` вҖ” Binary entry point with flags and graceful shutdown\n269: - [ ] `cmd/router/main.go` вҖ” Binary entry point with flags and graceful shutdown\n270: - [ ] `cmd/workload-manager/main.go` вҖ” Binary entry point with flags and graceful shutdown\n271: - [ ] `cmd/picod/main.go` вҖ” Binary entry point with flags and graceful shutdown\n272: - [ ] `pkg/common/signal` вҖ” Shared signal handling package\n273: - [ ] `pkg/common/version` вҖ” Shared version package\n274: - [ ] All 4 binaries compile successfully\n275: - [ ] All 4 binaries print help with `--help`\n276: - [ ] All 4 binaries handle SIGINT/SIGTERM gracefully\n277: \n278: ---\n279: \n280: ## References\n281: \n282: - [deployment/design.md](/deployment/design.md) вҖ” Build targets and Docker image specs\n283: - [AR-009/delta-spec.md](/changes/AR-009/delta-spec.md) вҖ” Router flags specification\n284: - [AR-007/delta-spec.md](/changes/AR-007/delta-spec.md) вҖ” Workload manager controller spec\n285: - [code-execution/spec.md](/code-execution/spec.md) вҖ” Picod server spec\n286: - [idle-cleanup/spec.md](/idle-cleanup/spec.md) вҖ” Agentd binary spec\n\n(End of file - total 286 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-019 вҖ” CLI дәҢиҝӣеҲ¶е…ҘеҸЈ (4 binaries)\n\n> **Module:** `cmd`  \n> **Language:** Go  \n> **Size:** M  \n> **Stage:** ST-3 (Design) Completed вҶ’ ST-4 (Implementation)  \n> **Base Spec:** project.md, deployment/design.md\n\n---\n\n## Overview\n\nAR-019 implements the CLI binary entry points for the 4 core AgentCube components:\n1. **agentd** - Idle cleanup controller binary\n2. **router** - Session routing proxy binary  \n3. **workload-manager** - Sandbox orchestration binary\n4. **picod** - Sandbox daemon binary\n\nEach binary SHALL parse CLI flags, initialize configuration, wire dependencies, start the respective service, and handle graceful shutdown via OS signals.\n","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-019/tasks.md","time":{"start":1775884365669,"end":1775884365694}}}}
