{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775884570044,"sessionID":"ses_2850b7bd3ffe3UepMOBdCsmkmc","part":{"id":"prt_d7af5104c001My3k3ec1yFZirB","messageID":"msg_d7af4efbf001PtXiaEO4wEOS46","sessionID":"ses_2850b7bd3ffe3UepMOBdCsmkmc","type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"toolu_functions.write:5","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/proposal.md","content":"# Proposal: AgentCube CLI Toolkit (kubectl-agentcube)\n\n## AR-020 вҖ” CLI pack е‘Ҫд»Ө\n\n| Field | Value |\n|-------|-------|\n| **Module** | `cmd/cli` |\n| **Language** | Python |\n| **Size** | M (Medium) |\n| **Status** | Proposed |\n\n---\n\n## Purpose\n\nImplement a comprehensive command-line interface (`kubectl-agentcube`) for packaging, building, publishing, invoking, and checking status of AI agents against AgentCube or standard Kubernetes. This proposal delivers:\n\n1. **`pack`** вҖ” Validates and prepares agent workspace, generates Dockerfiles, manages metadata\n2. **`build`** вҖ” Builds container images from packaged workspaces (local Docker or cloud builds)\n3. **`publish`** вҖ” Publishes/deploys agents to AgentCube (AgentRuntime CR) or standard Kubernetes\n4. **`invoke`** вҖ” Invokes published agents with JSON payloads\n5. **`status`** вҖ” Checks deployment status and displays information\n\nThe CLI provides developers with a unified tool for the complete AI agent lifecycle management, from local development to production deployment.\n\n---\n\n## Scope\n\n### In Scope\n\n| Item | Detail |\n|------|--------|\n| **CLI Commands** | 5 subcommands: `pack`, `build`, `publish`, `invoke`, `status` |\n| **CLI Framework** | Typer with Rich markup for enhanced UX |\n| **Metadata Management** | YAML-based agent configuration with Pydantic validation |\n| **Docker Integration** | Docker SDK for building, pushing, and managing images |\n| **Kubernetes Integration** | Client-go via Kubernetes Python SDK for CRD operations |\n| **Multi-Language Support** | Python and Java agent packaging |\n| **Provider Abstraction** | Support for `agentcube` (AgentRuntime CR) and `k8s` (Deployment/Service) providers |\n| **Workspace Validation** | Structure validation, dependency processing, Dockerfile generation |\n| **Error Handling** | Consistent error patterns with verbose mode and traceback support |\n| **Progress Indicators** | Rich Progress spinners for long-running operations |\n\n### Out of Scope\n\n- Interactive wizard mode for agent creation\n- Remote workspace synchronization\n- Multi-registry image mirroring\n- Built-in container registry\n- Hot-reload development mode\n- IDE integrations (VSCode/JetBrains plugins)\n- Web-based management UI\n- Automated testing framework for agents\n- Performance profiling tools\n- Cost estimation and billing integration\n\n---\n\n## Design\n\n### Package Layout\n\n| Path | Role | Lines (est.) |\n|------|------|--------------|\n| `pyproject.toml` | Project metadata, dependencies, console script mapping | ~80 |\n| `agentcube/__init__.py` | Package version, exports `app` and runtimes | ~30 |\n| `agentcube/cli/__init__.py` | CLI subpackage marker | ~10 |\n| `agentcube/cli/main.py` | Typer app, all commands, error handling | ~350 |\n| `agentcube/models/pack_models.py` | `MetadataOptions` dataclass | ~60 |\n| `agentcube/runtime/__init__.py` | Re-exports runtimes + `MetadataOptions` | ~20 |\n| `agentcube/runtime/pack_runtime.py` | `PackRuntime` implementation | ~280 |\n| `agentcube/runtime/build_runtime.py` | `BuildRuntime` implementation | ~200 |\n| `agentcube/runtime/publish_runtime.py` | `PublishRuntime` implementation | ~250 |\n| `agentcube/runtime/invoke_runtime.py` | `InvokeRuntime` implementation | ~180 |\n| `agentcube/runtime/status_runtime.py` | `StatusRuntime` implementation | ~120 |\n| `agentcube/services/__init__.py` | Services package docstring | ~15 |\n| `agentcube/services/metadata_service.py` | `AgentMetadata`, `MetadataService` | ~180 |\n| `agentcube/services/docker_service.py` | `DockerService` for image operations | ~220 |\n| `agentcube/services/k8s_provider.py` | `KubernetesProvider` for K8s deployments | ~200 |\n| `agentcube/services/agentcube_provider.py` | `AgentCubeProvider` for AgentRuntime CR | ~180 |\n| `agentcube/operations/__init__.py` | Placeholder module docstring | ~10 |\n| `examples/hello-agent/main.py` | Example Python agent | ~40 |\n| `examples/math-agent/main.py` | Example math agent | ~60 |\n\n### Architecture\n\n```\nв”Ңв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”җ\nв”Ӯ                     AgentCube CLI (kubectl-agentcube)                в”Ӯ\nв”Ӯ                                                                      в”Ӯ\nв”Ӯ  в”Ңв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”җ  в”Ңв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”җ  в”Ңв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”җ  в”Ңв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”җ в”Ӯ\nв”Ӯ  в”Ӯ    pack     в”Ӯ  в”Ӯ   build     в”Ӯ  в”Ӯ  publish    в”Ӯ  в”Ӯ   invoke    в”Ӯ в”Ӯ\nв”Ӯ  в”Ӯ  в”Ңв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”җв”Ӯ  в”Ӯ  в”Ңв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”җв”Ӯ  в”Ӯ  в”Ңв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”җв”Ӯ  в”Ӯ  в”Ңв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”җв”Ӯ в”Ӯ\nв”Ӯ  в”Ӯ  в”ӮPackRuntimeв”Ӯ  в”Ӯ  в”ӮBuildRuntimeв”Ӯ  в”Ӯ  в”ӮPublishRuntimeв”Ӯ  в”Ӯ  в”ӮInvokeRuntimeв”Ӯ в”Ӯ\nв”Ӯ  в”Ӯ  в””в”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”¬в”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”ҳв”Ӯ  в”Ӯ  в””в”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”¬в”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”ҳв”Ӯ  в”Ӯ  в””в”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”¬в”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”ҳв”Ӯ  в”Ӯ  в””в”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”¬в”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”ҳв”Ӯ в”Ӯ\nв”Ӯ  в””в”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”јв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”ҳ  в””в”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”јв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”ҳ  в””в”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”јв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”ҳ  в””в”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”јв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”ҳ в”Ӯ\nв”Ӯ          в”Ӯ                в”Ӯ                в”Ӯ                в”Ӯ       в”Ӯ\nв”Ӯ          в””в”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”ҙв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”ҙв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”ҳ       в”Ӯ\nв”Ӯ                              в”Ӯ                                       в”Ӯ\nв”Ӯ  в”Ңв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”ҙв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”җ  в”Ӯ\nв”Ӯ  в”Ӯ                         Services Layer                         в”Ӯ  в”Ӯ\nв”Ӯ  в”Ӯ  в”Ңв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”җ  в”Ңв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”җ  в”Ңв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”җ  в”Ӯ  в”Ӯ\nв”Ӯ  в”Ӯ  в”ӮMetadataServiceв”Ӯ  в”ӮDockerServiceв”Ӯ  в”ӮKubernetesProvider/      в”Ӯ  в”Ӯ  в”Ӯ\nв”Ӯ  в”Ӯ  в”Ӯ               в”Ӯ  в”Ӯ               в”Ӯ  в”ӮAgentCubeProvider        в”Ӯ  в”Ӯ  в”Ӯ\nв”Ӯ  в”Ӯ  в””в”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”ҳ  в””в”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”ҳ  в””в”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”ҳ  в”Ӯ  в”Ӯ\nв”Ӯ  в””в”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”ҳ  в”Ӯ\nв”Ӯ                              в”Ӯ                                       в”Ӯ\nв”Ӯ          в”Ңв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”јв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”җ                  в”Ӯ\nв”Ӯ          в–ј                   в–ј                   в–ј                  в”Ӯ\nв”Ӯ    в”Ңв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”җ      в”Ңв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”җ      в”Ңв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”җ        в”Ӯ\nв”Ӯ    в”Ӯ  Docker  в”Ӯ      в”Ӯ   K8s    в”Ӯ      в”Ӯ Agent Metadata   в”Ӯ        в”Ӯ\nв”Ӯ    в”Ӯ  Engine  в”Ӯ      в”Ӯ   API    в”Ӯ      в”Ӯ   (YAML/Pydantic)в”Ӯ        в”Ӯ\nв”Ӯ    в””в”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”ҳ      в””в”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”ҳ      в””в”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”ҳ        в”Ӯ\nв””в”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”ҳ\n```\n\n### Command Flows\n\n#### Pack Command Flow\n\n```\npack(workspace, options)\n    в”Ӯ\n    в–ј\nв”Ңв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”җ\nв”Ӯ Validate Workspace Structureв”Ӯ\nв”Ӯ - Directory exists          в”Ӯ\nв”Ӯ - Has source files (*.py)   в”Ӯ\nв””в”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”¬в”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”ҳ\n              в”Ӯ\n              в–ј\nв”Ңв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”җ\nв”Ӯ Load/Create Metadata        в”Ӯ\nв”Ӯ - Try agent_metadata.yaml   в”Ӯ\nв”Ӯ - Fallback to agent.yaml    в”Ӯ\nв”Ӯ - Create new if missing     в”Ӯ\nв””в”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”¬в”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”ҳ\n              в”Ӯ\n              в–ј\nв”Ңв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”җ\nв”Ӯ Apply CLI Option Overrides  в”Ӯ\nв”Ӯ --agent-name, --language,   в”Ӯ\nв”Ӯ --entrypoint, --port, etc.  в”Ӯ\nв””в”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”¬в”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”ҳ\n              в”Ӯ\n              в–ј\nв”Ңв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”җ\nв”Ӯ Validate Language Compatibilityв”Ӯ\nв”Ӯ - Python: check *.py files  в”Ӯ\nв”Ӯ - Java: check pom.xml       в”Ӯ\nв””в”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”¬в”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”ҳ\n              в”Ӯ\n              в–ј\nв”Ңв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”җ\nв”Ӯ Process Dependencies        в”Ӯ\nв”Ӯ - requirements.txt for Py   в”Ӯ\nв”Ӯ - pom.xml for Java          в”Ӯ\nв””в”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”¬в”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”ҳ\n              в”Ӯ\n              в–ј\nв”Ңв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”җ\nв”Ӯ Generate Dockerfile         в”Ӯ\nв”Ӯ - Language-specific templateв”Ӯ\nв””в”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”¬в”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”ҳ\n              в”Ӯ\n              в–ј\nв”Ңв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”җ\nв”Ӯ Update Pack Metadata        в”Ӯ\nв”Ӯ - Save agent_metadata.yaml  в”Ӯ\nв””в”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”¬в”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”ҳ\n              в”Ӯ\n              в–ј\nв”Ңв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”җ\nв”Ӯ Return Result               в”Ӯ\nв”Ӯ - agent_name, paths, status в”Ӯ\nв””в”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”ҳ\n```\n\n#### Build Command Flow\n\n```\nbuild(workspace, options)\n    в”Ӯ\n    в–ј\nв”Ңв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”җ\nв”Ӯ Load Metadata               в”Ӯ\nв”Ӯ - Read agent_metadata.yaml  в”Ӯ\nв””в”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”¬в”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”ҳ\n              в”Ӯ\n              в–ј\nв”Ңв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”җ\nв”Ӯ Validate Prerequisites      в”Ӯ\nв”Ӯ - Docker available?         в”Ӯ\nв”Ӯ - Metadata has image info?  в”Ӯ\nв””в”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”¬в”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”ҳ\n              в”Ӯ\n              в–ј\nв”Ңв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”җ\nв”Ӯ Increment Version           в”Ӯ\nв”Ӯ - Patch bump (X.Y.Z вҶ’ X.Y.Z+1)\nв””в”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”¬в”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”ҳ\n              в”Ӯ\n              в”ңв”Җ local в”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв–ә Build with Docker SDK\n              в”Ӯ                   - Tag: agent_name:version\n              в”Ӯ                   - Build context: workspace\n              в”Ӯ\n              в””в”Җ cloud в”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв–ә Cloud provider build API\n                                  - Submit build job\n                                  - Wait for completion\n              в”Ӯ\n              в–ј\nв”Ңв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”җ\nв”Ӯ Update Build Metadata       в”Ӯ\nв”Ӯ - Record build info, tag    в”Ӯ\nв””в”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”¬в”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”ҳ\n              в”Ӯ\n              в–ј\n        Return Result\n```\n\n#### Publish Command Flow\n\n```\npublish(workspace, options)\n    в”Ӯ\n    в–ј\nв”Ңв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”җ\nв”Ӯ Load Metadata               в”Ӯ\nв”Ӯ - Read agent_metadata.yaml  в”Ӯ\nв””в”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”¬в”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”ҳ\n              в”Ӯ\n              в–ј\nв”Ңв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”җ\nв”Ӯ Prepare Image               в”Ӯ\nв”Ӯ - Local: push to registry   в”Ӯ\nв”Ӯ - Cloud: use image_url      в”Ӯ\nв””в”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”¬в”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”ҳ\n              в”Ӯ\n              в”ңв”Җ provider=agentcube в”Җв”Җв”Җв–ә Deploy AgentRuntime CR\n              в”Ӯ                          - Create/update CR\n              в”Ӯ                          - Wait for readiness\n              в”Ӯ                          - Update metadata\n              в”Ӯ\n              в””в”Җ provider=k8s в”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв–ә Deploy Deployment + Service\n                                         - Create Deployment\n                                         - Create NodePort Service\n                                         - Wait for rollout\n                                         - Update metadata\n              в”Ӯ\n              в–ј\n        Return Result\n```\n\n#### Invoke Command Flow\n\n```\ninvoke(workspace, payload, headers)\n    в”Ӯ\n    в–ј\nв”Ңв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”җ\nв”Ӯ Validate Prerequisites      в”Ӯ\nв”Ӯ - Metadata has agent_id?    в”Ӯ\nв”Ӯ - Deployment published?     в”Ӯ\nв””в”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”¬в”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”ҳ\n              в”Ӯ\n              в–ј\nв”Ңв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”җ\nв”Ӯ Determine Endpoint          в”Ӯ\nв”Ӯ - agentcube: router_url     в”Ӯ\nв”Ӯ - k8s: node_port service    в”Ӯ\nв””в”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”¬в”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”ҳ\n              в”Ӯ\n              в”ңв”Җ provider=agentcube в”Җв”Җв”Җв–ә POST to AgentRuntime\n              в”Ӯ                          - /v1/namespaces/{ns}/\n              в”Ӯ                            agent-runtimes/{name}/invocations/\n              в”Ӯ                          - Add X-Agentcube-Session-Id header\n              в”Ӯ\n              в””в”Җ provider=k8s в”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв–ә POST to Service endpoint\n                                         - http://localhost:{node_port}\n                                         - Direct HTTP invocation\n              в”Ӯ\n              в–ј\n        Return Response\n```\n\n---\n\n## Interface\n\n### Console Script Entry Point\n\n```toml\n[project.scripts]\nkubectl-agentcube = \"agentcube.cli.main:app\"\n```\n\n### Global CLI Options\n\n| Option | Type | Default | Description |\n|--------|------|---------|-------------|\n| `--version` | bool | None | Show version and exit (eager option) |\n| `--verbose` / `-v` | bool | False | Enable verbose output with DEBUG logging |\n\n### Pack Command\n\n| Option | Type | Default | Description |\n|--------|------|---------|-------------|\n| `-f`, `--workspace` | str | \".\" | Path to agent workspace directory |\n| `--agent-name` | str | None | Override the agent name |\n| `--language` | str | None | Programming language (python, java) |\n| `--entrypoint` | str | None | Override the entrypoint command |\n| `--port` | int | None | Port to expose in Dockerfile |\n| `--build-mode` | str | None | Build strategy: local or cloud |\n| `--description` | str | None | Agent description |\n| `--output` | str | None | Output path for packaged workspace |\n| `--verbose` | bool | False | Enable detailed logging |\n\n### Build Command\n\n| Option | Type | Default | Description |\n|--------|------|---------|-------------|\n| `-f`, `--workspace` | str | \".\" | Path to agent workspace directory |\n| `-p`, `--proxy` | str | None | Custom proxy URL for dependency resolution |\n| `--cloud-provider` | str | None | Cloud provider name (e.g., huawei) |\n| `--output` | str | None | Output path for build artifacts |\n| `--verbose` | bool | False | Enable detailed logging |\n\n### Publish Command\n\n| Option | Type | Default | Description |\n|--------|------|---------|-------------|\n| `-f`, `--workspace` | str | \".\" | Path to agent workspace directory |\n| `--version` | str | None | Semantic version string (e.g., v1.0.0) |\n| `--image-url` | str | None | Image repository URL (required in local build mode) |\n| `--image-username` | str | None | Username for image repository |\n| `--image-password` | str | None | Password for image repository |\n| `--description` | str | None | Agent description |\n| `--region` | str | None | Deployment region |\n| `--cloud-provider` | str | None | Cloud provider name |\n| `--provider` | str | \"agentcube\" | Target provider: 'agentcube' or 'k8s' |\n| `--node-port` | int | None | Specific NodePort (30000-32767) for K8s |\n| `--replicas` | int | None | Number of replicas for K8s deployment |\n| `--namespace` | str | None | Namespace for deployment |\n| `--verbose` | bool | False | Enable detailed logging |\n\n### Invoke Command\n\n| Option | Type | Default | Description |\n|--------|------|---------|-------------|\n| `-f`, `--workspace` | str | \".\" | Path to agent workspace directory |\n| `--payload` | str | \"{}\" | JSON-formatted input passed to agent |\n| `--header` | List[str] | None | Custom HTTP headers (repeatable) |\n| `--provider` | str | \"agentcube\" | Target provider: 'agentcube' or 'k8s' |\n| `--verbose` | bool | False | Enable detailed logging |\n\n### Status Command\n\n| Option | Type | Default | Description |\n|--------|------|---------|-------------|\n| `-f`, `--workspace` | str | \".\" | Path to agent workspace directory |\n| `--provider` | str | \"agentcube\" | Target provider: 'agentcube' or 'k8s' |\n| `--verbose` | bool | False | Enable detailed logging |\n\n---\n\n## Data Models\n\n### AgentMetadata (Pydantic BaseModel)\n\n| Field | Type | Default | Description |\n|-------|------|---------|-------------|\n| `agent_name` | str | required | Unique name identifying the agent |\n| `description` | Optional[str] | None | Human-readable summary |\n| `language` | str | \"python\" | Programming language (python/java) |\n| `entrypoint` | str | required | Command to launch the agent |\n| `port` | int | 8080 | Port exposed by agent runtime |\n| `build_mode` | str | \"local\" | Build strategy: local or cloud |\n| `region` | Optional[str] | None | Deployment region |\n| `version` | Optional[str] | None | Semantic version for publishing |\n| `image` | Optional[Dict] | None | Container image information |\n| `auth` | Optional[Dict] | None | Authentication configuration |\n| `requirements_file` | Optional[str] | \"requirements.txt\" | Python dependency file |\n| `registry_url` | Optional[str] | \"\" | Registry URL for image publishing |\n| `registry_username` | Optional[str] | \"\" | Registry username |\n| `registry_password` | Optional[str] | \"\" | Registry password |\n| `agent_endpoint` | Optional[str] | None | Agent endpoint URL |\n| `workload_manager_url` | Optional[str] | None | URL for Workload Manager |\n| `router_url` | Optional[str] | None | URL for Router |\n| `readiness_probe_path` | Optional[str] | None | Path for readiness probe |\n| `readiness_probe_port` | Optional[int] | None | Port for readiness probe |\n| `agent_id` | Optional[str] | None | Agent ID assigned by AgentCube |\n| `session_id` | Optional[str] | None | Session ID for the agent |\n| `k8s_deployment` | Optional[Dict] | None | Kubernetes deployment information |\n\n**Validators:**\n- `validate_language` вҶ’ lowercase, must be 'python' or 'java'\n- `validate_build_mode` вҶ’ lowercase, must be 'local' or 'cloud'\n- `validate_port` вҶ’ must be 1..65535\n\n### MetadataOptions (Dataclass)\n\n| Field | Type | Default |\n|-------|------|---------|\n| `agent_name` | Optional[str] | None |\n| `language` | Optional[str] | 'python' |\n| `entrypoint` | Optional[str] | None |\n| `port` | Optional[int] | 8080 |\n| `build_mode` | Optional[str] | 'local' |\n| `requirements_file` | Optional[str] | None |\n| `description` | Optional[str] | None |\n| `workload_manager_url` | Optional[str] | \"\" |\n| `router_url` | Optional[str] | \"\" |\n| `readiness_probe_path` | Optional[str] | \"\" |\n| `readiness_probe_port` | Optional[int] | 8080 |\n| `registry_url` | Optional[str] | \"\" |\n| `registry_username` | Optional[str] | \"\" |\n| `registry_password` | Optional[str] | \"\" |\n| `agent_endpoint` | Optional[str] | \"\" |\n\n---\n\n## Error Handling\n\n### Error Patterns\n\n| Error | Description | Handling |\n|-------|-------------|----------|\n| `ValueError` | Invalid input, missing required fields | Print in red, exit code 1 |\n| `RuntimeError` | Docker/K8s operation failures | Print in red, exit code 1 |\n| `FileNotFoundError` | Missing workspace/metadata files | Print guidance, exit code 1 |\n| `ValidationError` | Pydantic validation failures | Print field errors, exit code 1 |\n| `ConnectionError` | Network/registry failures | Print with retry suggestion, exit code 1 |\n| `TimeoutError` | K8s deployment readiness timeout | Print timeout message, exit code 1 |\n\n### Error Handler Function\n\n```python\ndef _handle_error(e: Exception, command_name: str, verbose: bool) -> None:\n    \"\"\"Print error and exit with code 1.\"\"\"\n    # Print \"Error {command_name}: {e}\" in red\n    # If verbose, print full traceback\n    # raise typer.Exit(1)\n```\n\n### Exit Codes\n\n| Exit Code | Meaning |\n|-----------|---------|\n| 0 | Success |\n| 1 | General error (validation, runtime) |\n| 2 | Missing dependencies (Docker, K8s) |\n| 130 | Interrupted (SIGINT) |\n\n---\n\n## Security Considerations\n\n### Sensitive Data Handling\n\n| Data | Storage | Transmission |\n|------|---------|--------------|\n| Registry passwords | Environment variables only | HTTPS with TLS |\n| Kubernetes tokens | kubeconfig or in-cluster SA | mTLS when available |\n| Agent session IDs | Local metadata file | Header encryption |\n| Image pull secrets | Kubernetes secrets | Cluster-internal only |\n\n### RBAC Requirements (for Kubernetes Provider)\n\n| Resource | Verbs |\n|----------|-------|\n| `deployments` | `get`, `list`, `watch`, `create`, `update`, `patch`, `delete` |\n| `services` | `get`, `list`, `watch`, `create`, `update`, `patch`, `delete` |\n| `agentruntimes` (CR) | `get`, `list`, `watch`, `create`, `update`, `patch`, `delete` |\n| `pods` | `get`, `list`, `watch` |\n| `secrets` | `get`, `list`, `create`, `update` |\n\n### Dockerfile Security\n\n- Use official base images (python:3.x-slim, openjdk:xx-jre-slim)\n- Run as non-root user where possible\n- Pin package versions in requirements.txt\n- Minimize layer count\n- Scan images before publishing (out of scope, recommended)\n\n---\n\n## Impact Analysis\n\n### Files Created\n\n| File | Lines (est.) | Description |\n|------|--------------|-------------|\n| `pyproject.toml` | ~80 | Package metadata and dependencies |\n| `agentcube/__init__.py` | ~30 | Package exports |\n| `agentcube/cli/__init__.py` | ~10 | CLI subpackage marker |\n| `agentcube/cli/main.py` | ~350 | Main CLI with all commands |\n| `agentcube/models/pack_models.py` | ~60 | MetadataOptions dataclass |\n| `agentcube/runtime/__init__.py` | ~20 | Runtime re-exports |\n| `agentcube/runtime/pack_runtime.py` | ~280 | PackRuntime implementation |\n| `agentcube/runtime/build_runtime.py` | ~200 | BuildRuntime implementation |\n| `agentcube/runtime/publish_runtime.py` | ~250 | PublishRuntime implementation |\n| `agentcube/runtime/invoke_runtime.py` | ~180 | InvokeRuntime implementation |\n| `agentcube/runtime/status_runtime.py` | ~120 | StatusRuntime implementation |\n| `agentcube/services/__init__.py` | ~15 | Services package docstring |\n| `agentcube/services/metadata_service.py` | ~180 | AgentMetadata and MetadataService |\n| `agentcube/services/docker_service.py` | ~220 | Docker SDK wrapper |\n| `agentcube/services/k8s_provider.py` | ~200 | Kubernetes Deployment/Service provider |\n| `agentcube/services/agentcube_provider.py` | ~180 | AgentRuntime CR provider |\n| `agentcube/operations/__init__.py` | ~10 | Operations placeholder |\n| `examples/hello-agent/main.py` | ~40 | Example agent |\n| `examples/math-agent/main.py` | ~60 | Example math agent |\n| **Total** | **~2,715** | |\n\n### Dependencies\n\n```toml\n[project]\ndependencies = [\n    \"typer[all]>=0.9.0\",\n    \"pydantic>=2.0.0\",\n    \"pyyaml>=6.0\",\n    \"httpx>=0.24.0\",\n    \"docker>=6.0.0\",\n    \"rich>=13.0.0\",\n    \"packaging>=23.0\",\n    \"importlib-resources>=6.0.0\",\n    \"semver>=3.0.0\",\n]\n\n[project.optional-dependencies]\nk8s = [\"kubernetes>=28.0.0\"]\ndev = [\n    \"pytest>=7.4.0\",\n    \"pytest-asyncio>=0.21.0\",\n    \"pytest-cov>=4.1.0\",\n    \"ruff>=0.1.0\",\n    \"mypy>=1.5.0\",\n    \"pre-commit>=3.3.0\",\n    \"kubernetes>=28.0.0\",\n]\ntest = [\n    \"pytest>=7.4.0\",\n    \"pytest-asyncio>=0.21.0\",\n    \"pytest-cov>=4.1.0\",\n    \"pytest-mock>=3.11.0\",\n    \"httpx-mock>=0.10.0\",\n]\n```\n\n### Downstream Consumers\n\n| Consumer | Usage |\n|----------|-------|\n| Agent Developers | Package, build, publish agents locally |\n| CI/CD Pipelines | Automated agent builds and deployments |\n| Helm Charts | Pre-deployment validation and packaging |\n| Documentation | Example commands and workflows |\n\n### Performance Characteristics\n\n| Operation | Time (est.) | Notes |\n|-----------|-------------|-------|\n| `pack` | <1s | Workspace validation and Dockerfile generation |\n| `build` (local) | 30s-5min | Depends on image size and network |\n| `build` (cloud) | 2-10min | Depends on cloud provider queue |\n| `publish` (k8s) | 30s-2min | Image push + deployment rollout |\n| `publish` (agentcube) | 10s-1min | CR creation + readiness check |\n| `invoke` | <100ms | HTTP request to running agent |\n| `status` | <1s | K8s API query |\n\n---\n\n## Alternatives Considered\n\n### Alternative 1: Pure Go CLI\n\n| Aspect | Evaluation |\n|--------|------------|\n| **Pros** | Single language codebase; smaller binary; faster startup; easier cross-compilation |\n| **Cons** | Docker SDK less mature in Go; more boilerplate; steeper learning curve for Python developers; Kubernetes SDK more verbose |\n| **Decision** | **Rejected** вҖ” Python offers better ecosystem for CLI tooling (Typer/Rich), more mature Docker SDK, easier scripting integration |\n\n### Alternative 2: Separate CLIs per Command\n\n| Aspect | Evaluation |\n|--------|------------|\n| **Pros** | Smaller individual binaries; independent versioning; focused scope |\n| **Cons** | Duplicated code; more packages to maintain; inconsistent UX; harder to discover |\n| **Decision** | **Rejected** вҖ” Unified CLI provides better developer experience, shared code, consistent patterns |\n\n### Alternative 3: kubectl Plugin Architecture\n\n| Aspect | Evaluation |\n|--------|------------|\n| **Pros** | Native kubectl integration; familiar to K8s users; leverages kubectl config |\n| **Cons** | Requires kubectl installation; limited to K8s workflows; harder to implement non-K8s features |\n| **Decision** | **Rejected** вҖ” Standalone CLI (`kubectl-agentcube`) provides more flexibility, works without kubectl for local development |\n\n### Alternative 4: Web-Based Dashboard\n\n| Aspect | Evaluation |\n|--------|------------|\n| **Pros** | Rich UI; visual feedback; easier for beginners; no local installation |\n| **Cons** | Requires backend service; network dependency; harder to script; more complex architecture |\n| **Decision** | **Rejected** вҖ” CLI is prerequisite for automation and CI/CD; web UI can be added later as separate component |\n\n---\n\n## Risks and Mitigations\n\n| Risk | Likelihood | Impact | Mitigation |\n|------|------------|--------|------------|\n| Docker SDK compatibility issues | Medium | Medium | Pin docker>=6.0.0; test on multiple Docker versions |\n| Kubernetes SDK authentication edge cases | Medium | High | Support kubeconfig, in-cluster, and env-based auth; clear error messages |\n| Cross-platform path handling | Medium | Medium | Use `pathlib.Path` consistently; test on Windows/Linux/macOS |\n| Metadata format evolution | Medium | Medium | Pydantic validators; migration utilities; version field in metadata |\n| Python version compatibility | Low | Medium | Require Python>=3.10; test matrix in CI |\n| Large workspace packaging | Medium | Low | .dockerignore support; size warnings; exclude patterns |\n| Registry authentication failures | Medium | High | Retry with exponential backoff; clear credential prompts |\n| Concurrent metadata modifications | Low | Medium | File locking or atomic writes; last-write-wins with warnings |\n\n---\n\n## Verification\n\n### Installation Verification\n\n```bash\n# Install the CLI\npip install -e ./cmd/cli\n\n# Verify entry point\nwhich kubectl-agentcube\nkubectl-agentcube --version\n```\n\n### Pack Command Verification\n\n```bash\n# Create test workspace\nmkdir -p /tmp/test-agent\ncat > /tmp/test-agent/main.py << 'EOF'\nfrom flask import Flask\napp = Flask(__name__)\n\n@app.route('/invoke', methods=['POST'])\ndef invoke():\n    return {\"message\": \"Hello from agent\"}\n\nif __name__ == '__main__':\n    app.run(host='0.0.0.0', port=8080)\nEOF\n\n# Pack the agent\nkubectl-agentcube pack -f /tmp/test-agent --agent-name test-agent --language python\n\n# Verify metadata created\nls /tmp/test-agent/agent_metadata.yaml\nls /tmp/test-agent/Dockerfile\n```\n\n### Build Command Verification\n\n```bash\n# Build the agent (requires Docker)\nkubectl-agentcube build -f /tmp/test-agent --verbose\n\n# Verify Docker image\ndocker images | grep test-agent\n```\n\n### Publish Command Verification (requires K8s)\n\n```bash\n# Publish to Kubernetes\nkubectl-agentcube publish -f /tmp/test-agent \\\n  --provider k8s \\\n  --namespace default \\\n  --image-url myregistry/test-agent:latest\n\n# Verify deployment\nkubectl get deployment test-agent\nkubectl get service test-agent\n```\n\n### Invoke Command Verification\n\n```bash\n# Invoke the agent\nkubectl-agentcube invoke -f /tmp/test-agent \\\n  --payload '{\"input\": \"hello\"}' \\\n  --provider k8s\n```\n\n### Status Command Verification\n\n```bash\n# Check status\nkubectl-agentcube status -f /tmp/test-agent --provider k8s\n```\n\n### Error Handling Verification\n\n```bash\n# Test missing workspace\nkubectl-agentcube pack -f /nonexistent 2>&1 | grep -q \"Error\" && echo \"Error handling works\"\n\n# Test invalid JSON payload\nkubectl-agentcube invoke -f /tmp/test-agent --payload 'invalid json' 2>&1 | grep -q \"JSON\" && echo \"JSON validation works\"\n\n# Test verbose mode\nkubectl-agentcube pack -f /tmp/test-agent --verbose 2>&1 | grep -q \"DEBUG\" && echo \"Verbose mode works\"\n```\n\n---\n\n## References\n\n- [cli-toolkit/design.md](cli-toolkit/design.md) вҖ” Detailed design specifications\n- [cli-toolkit/spec.md](cli-toolkit/spec.md) вҖ” Complete requirements specification\n- [python-sdk/design.md](python-sdk/design.md) вҖ” Python SDK for programmatic access\n- [deployment/client-go.md](deployment/client-go.md) вҖ” Kubernetes client patterns\n- [project.md](project.md) вҖ” Project context and architecture\n\n---\n\n## Success Criteria\n\n1. вң… All 5 CLI commands (`pack`, `build`, `publish`, `invoke`, `status`) are implemented\n2. вң… Typer app initializes with proper help text and version display\n3. вң… Global `--verbose` flag enables DEBUG logging\n4. вң… `pack` validates workspace structure and generates Dockerfile\n5. вң… `pack` creates/updates `agent_metadata.yaml` with Pydantic validation\n6. вң… `build` supports both local Docker and cloud build modes\n7. вң… `publish` supports both `agentcube` (AgentRuntime CR) and `k8s` (Deployment) providers\n8. вң… `invoke` correctly POSTs JSON payload and handles session headers\n9. вң… `status` displays Rich Table with deployment information\n10. вң… All commands use consistent error handling with `_handle_error`\n11. вң… Metadata loading falls back through `agent_metadata.yaml` вҶ’ `agent.yaml` вҶ’ `metadata.yaml`\n12. вң… Python and Java language support with appropriate Dockerfile templates\n13. вң… Docker image operations work with registry authentication\n14. вң… Kubernetes provider creates Deployment + NodePort Service correctly\n15. вң… AgentCube provider creates AgentRuntime CR with proper spec\n16. вң… All runtime classes follow spec: `PackRuntime`, `BuildRuntime`, `PublishRuntime`, `InvokeRuntime`, `StatusRuntime`\n17. вң… Services layer properly abstracted: `MetadataService`, `DockerService`, `KubernetesProvider`, `AgentCubeProvider`\n18. вң… Package structure follows spec with proper `__init__.py` exports\n19. вң… `kubectl-agentcube` console script entry point works after pip install\n20. вң… Examples directory contains working `hello-agent` and `math-agent`\n\n---\n\n*AR-020 вҖ” Module: cmd/cli вҖ” Language: Python вҖ” Size: M*\n"},"output":"Wrote file 