{"type":"text","timestamp":1775884594822,"sessionID":"ses_2850b7bd3ffe3UepMOBdCsmkmc","part":{"id":"prt_d7af84eb20016L90iaJo2LXeLr","messageID":"msg_d7af80df3001GJ5U611Rd0hq4d","sessionID":"ses_2850b7bd3ffe3UepMOBdCsmkmc","type":"text","text":"I've created the `proposal.md` file for AR-020 вҖ” CLI pack command. The proposal covers:\n\n## Summary\n\n**AR-020 вҖ” CLI pack е‘Ҫд»Ө** is a Python-based CLI toolkit (`kubectl-agentcube`) for the complete AI agent lifecycle management.\n\n### Key Components\n\n| Command | Purpose |\n|---------|---------|\n| `pack` | Validates workspace, generates Dockerfile, manages metadata |\n| `build` | Builds container images (local Docker or cloud) |\n| `publish` | Deploys to AgentCube (AgentRuntime CR) or K8s (Deployment/Service) |\n| `invoke` | Invokes agents with JSON payloads |\n| `status` | Checks deployment status |\n\n### Architecture Highlights\n\n- **CLI Framework**: Typer with Rich markup\n- **Data Validation**: Pydantic models for metadata\n- **Docker Integration**: Docker SDK for image operations\n- **Kubernetes**: Python client-go for CRD operations\n- **Multi-Language**: Python and Java support\n\n### Files to be Created\n\n- ~2,715 lines across 19 Python files\n- Package structure: `agentcube/cli/`, `agentcube/runtime/`, `agentcube/services/`, `agentcube/models/`\n- Console script: `kubectl-agentcube`\n\n### Dependencies\n\n- Core: `typer[all]>=0.9.0`, `pydantic>=2.0.0`, `docker>=6.0.0`, `rich>=13.0.0`\n- Optional: `kubernetes>=28.0.0` for K8s operations\n\nThe proposal includes detailed command flows, interface specifications, error handling patterns, security considerations, and 20 success criteria for verification.","time":{"start":1775884594819,"end":1775884594819}}}
